JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) – The CEO of Vedanta-controlled Konkola Copper Mines (KCM), Steven Din, will join Strategic and Precious Metals Processing (SPMP) as CEO on August 1. He will lead SPMP’s new Oman antimony and gold processing facility, which is coming into production. “We welcome Steven’s arrival at this important time in the project as we start production at our state-of-the art facility.  Steven’s wealth of experience and leadership skills will now drive our strategy forward to establish SPMP as a significant global player in the industry,” said chairperson Khalid Al Yamadi. Earlier this week, Dheshnee Naidoo was appointed CEO of Vedanta Resources’ Africa Base Metals, a role that will see her be CEO of KCM as well as other Vedanta entities.